{"key":"post-16132131","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>16132131</id>\n<content>&lt;img style=&quot;max-width:192px;height:auto;&quot; src=&quot;/forums/images/lock.gif&quot;&gt; &lt;b&gt;This thread has been closed.&lt;/b&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Reason:&lt;br /&gt;We always welcome people making contributions, but please wait until you have a few grows under your belt.&amp;nbsp; There's just too many mistakes to let it stand.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Needles should be flame sterilized.&amp;nbsp; It matters not if a needle is sterile out of the package-it is no longer sterile after the first inoculation and can carry contamination from one jar to the next if flame sterilization isn't used.&amp;nbsp; Alcohol only gets the outside of the needle, not the inside.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The oven tek is bogus and leads to a higher rate of contamination.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If the water is 40% up a brf tek jar, the substrate will get saturated.&amp;nbsp; Elevate jars out of the water totally.&amp;nbsp; It's the steam which sterilizes, not the water.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Taping jar holes is recommended.&amp;nbsp; Use breathable micropore tape.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Light does effect colonization.&amp;nbsp; Low level ambient light speeds it up, while very bright light slows it down.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;One should not harvest all the mushrooms on a cake at once.&amp;nbsp; Pick as they're ready.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;There's a few more, but this is enough.&amp;nbsp; Get a few grows, work out your technique and then help the new folks out.&amp;nbsp; I can tell you've done a lot of reading and this is good.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next></next>\n<prev>16132098</prev>\n<first>16131521</first>\n<last>16132131</last>\n<when>1335270155</when>\n<utime>04/24/12 03:22 PM</utime>\n</post>"}